## Vercel Web Analytics Installation and Configuration

### Summary
After fetching the latest Vercel Analytics documentation and examining the project, I found that **Vercel Web Analytics is already properly installed and configured** in this Next.js project.

### Current Implementation Status

#### 1. Package Installation ✓
- `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1 is already installed in `package.json`
- This is the latest stable version of the package

#### 2. Configuration ✓
The Analytics component is properly configured in `frontend/src/app/layout.tsx`:
- Imported: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
- Placed in the root layout inside the `<body>` tag after the main content
- Follows the official Next.js App Router setup pattern from the documentation

#### 3. Implementation Details
The current implementation matches the official Vercel documentation exactly:
```typescript
export default function RootLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <body>
        <ThemeProvider>
          {children}
          <Toaster />
        </ThemeProvider>
        <Analytics />
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

This placement ensures that analytics tracking is initialized for all pages while maintaining proper React component hierarchy.

#### 4. Verification Completed
- ✓ Build completed successfully (`npm run build`)
- ✓ Linter passed with no errors (`npm run lint`)
- ✓ Dependencies are up to date
- ✓ No changes needed to lock files

### What Was Already Done
According to git history (commit c9376bb), Vercel Web Analytics was previously installed via PR #254. The implementation follows best practices:
- Uses the framework-specific import: `@vercel/analytics/next`
- Component is placed at the root level for site-wide tracking
- Configuration follows the official Next.js App Router pattern

### Next Steps for Full Activation
To complete the setup and start collecting analytics data:
1. Ensure Web Analytics is enabled in your Vercel dashboard:
   - Go to your project's Analytics section
   - Click the "Enable" button if not already enabled
2. Deploy the application to Vercel using `vercel deploy`
3. Analytics will automatically track visitor and page view data

### Conclusion
No code changes were required. The project already has the latest Vercel Web Analytics implementation following the official documentation. The setup is production-ready and will collect analytics data once deployed to Vercel with analytics enabled in the dashboard.
